 stack that does not tie up cpu_resources with its 1 hour (3600,000)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="|$sAQ)hEtTy%(zGI5gYu"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="V~hPe%#rL{av@rgsT,@X"><field name="TEXT">Also the 'if(false)' mini-stacks will be skipped by cpu, for further non-resource burdening</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="}p)]zs5-wPknR.F6*5V@"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="]RJsV1XK7iK9|3FAQf|p"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id="vvUb4Z)Wg[SLq3Gw%+E="><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="9APQ{$p$Y@RvoeJDj~:{"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Very Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="PZu/KE^+SnVAmB`+ya~,"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="[~xn/k;5-TUxGtKIkG5n"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="~FUbvow,Owj=8XA1omK("><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id=",8zjx6NGaR:5B/R:-V9M"><field name="TEXT">Levels 1, 2, 2.1</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="hBh,aHf6Y#Y=/FK!q;{d"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="}4p..a(,~6:8tjg=]4))"><field name="TEXT">* Level 1: Hardcoded Static via Actual_Numbers for MotorPower%</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="ijbssOX2H63BbqesTV%?"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="N,SqK%ERkpg26Shmqh_@"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2: Softcoded Dynamic via Variables/Constants for MotorPower% </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="vmg+:t,1]q,4x?xxTm]y"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="t^_EpP~.|;Z4zKaHbkUK"><field name="TEXT">* Level 2.1 Add Controller_Joystick * Level 2.2 Add Gear 3 (90%?)</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="okYLpAf!s1F)=-:W$v%{"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="m)9(E=(h^rwi^%lYfVTm"><field name="TEXT">Basic Comment_Colors Usage:: Black: Very Big Picture, Blue: Big Picture, Green: Following Block_Code Moddable, Orange: Question/TODO, Magenta: Special Multi-Purpose </field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="IPL1]@Vs^i6WLMs6azB?"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="#jj:j6n=6f`Kn`-,AEPN"><field name="TEXT">micro:bit Ver2 Warning during Download is Ignorable Yet Courteously Helpful</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="xERHuj1b-W]n*NwBQ)s|"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="4e_,-5$~A%]Ca6pr_O@:"><field name="TEXT">'if_then' mini-stacks useful for modular 3-D code select/duplicate/move/delete</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="dBp+;ZT)mLouCtT7TZ}0"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="$;`[U,O]#_Fini-I{2Jd"><field name="TEXT">Light_Gray Functions non-editable (backend staff-use code only)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="(;wN/U}j(fm8c37yq^k$"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="heE;tj$kl~0dLy#+Sb/0"><field name="TEXT">For Group_CHannel_# (Bot_Id): Propose: 1-10 Staff Use, 11-99 Student Use</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="G)+%DJjj%ziIBcDq~U.:"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="$;B9c;jU(;oRNmVw0DXV"><field name="TEXT">SW Reset: Long_Press Logo for 3 sec min</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="vxfWeMz4jYwAUUT~oxhB"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="a_MqwNCDWMYp@_Ko6`U;"><field name="TEXT">Built-in Diagnostic Test: Short_Press Logo for 1 sec max</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="5J*Q!uUUZHgdI6QA[tic"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="`U)Vc)88OY?rzTSOw0|,"><field name="TEXT">'Blocks' Window homes 'on start'_stack as top_left corner of editor_screen, until 'on start' is moved below, then next stack to right presides</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="WF@K]PL4XpR/2y@7Un$@"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="~BwQL!HNh),^`;2~Li{~"><field name="TEXT">All These Levels are Intermediate Level Coding due to Networking Pairing Involved.  Basic Diagnostic Servo_Motors (Autonomoous) is Beginner Level.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="L:{1XbQ4;pcKn)Eoc2UI"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="QrG_U.f[etb$f+.c]HPz"><field name="TEXT">This Intermediate Level Network_Pairing has 1sec_Lag Response Time; The Other Advanced Level Network_Pairing has Real_Time Response Time.</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="W[]NEiP,Ddl@YGWX9+8="><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="a{mp}d)Sr]Q-+$[:wRpG"><field name="TEXT">For Level 1, can keep 'Forward: set manual_servo_motors' Block functional, yet reset to 0 all other 'set manual_servo_motors' Blocks for Discovery Learning</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="pCJhGVXJrrh@^Ca|3e]x"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="9`hEF#TEa)^D0UzojLPc"><field name="TEXT">If duplicate stacks exist, then the highest stack is active and others are non_active</field></shadow></value></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></next></block></statement><next><block type="controls_if" id="]vw%l/ESxOk[xMVYZr=]"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="Op)tmS;/kDK3SHeh.]5M"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_6_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Big_Func" id=".5mHV%$@S].+@|p:F];."><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="~prWCh4Mp3ORf`@:(7=w"><field name="TEXT">Staff: Important Notes</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="O|i/-sCC=iADsQQ@UyTH"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="Q-L#@,ZV$F}dmS@WY=yK"><field name="TEXT">Upon open file, Editor zooms in on closest stack to right of original_origin from project_creation</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="._|`qKepk6c:x6.RPcn,"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="PmK2}JeAo?7q9M[G`X,c"><field name="TEXT">Semantic Naming prefers '_' vs. '-' since latter can be conufused with minus_sign</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="yvz,!AOTZ(EQom8?(=Nf"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="xu$~l[Im@$n_jTxP^0qt"><field name="TEXT">'every 360000 ms' (1 hour) Stacks can be ignored, esp w/ 'if false' embedded</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="e:Q[@J}`P2L4%y8dDt(."><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="oqBz6SsEY1!aHER$f/bC"><field name="TEXT">Avoid using 'show leds' Block since will cause lag &amp; degrade real-time response</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="L}Bp{q9AJ6}73f~xQa+h"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="L_l?@F|4]L!ff=Po]Qoj"><field name="TEXT">Seems like 'signficant' changes to JavaScript can activate 'format code', rearrange stacks to original position</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="0*Y3wujvH?h)LUngCeaW"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="24gYW2+KHuN:6r9x**^O"><field name="TEXT">Important 'system' variables are 1) _system_Hw_DeviceType__* (Hw=Hardware) and 2) _system_Sw_ModeState__* (Sw=Software)</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="3MKFnPv-c/%PmOi#ib5*"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="78TL~~Xd}[q~jB%uv53g"><field name="TEXT">If Buttons C-F for Gears/Misc, Maybe 'Logo Up/Down' for 'Servo_Arm Up/Down'</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="`QTzo.h;4+j9xel|0d)f"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="g+1lo;c=fWNwmz0c8pUJ"><field name="TEXT">'Rotatedisplay' could be used on Bot's Led_Screen, but causes light flickering on bottom row, so maybe avoid</field></shadow></value><next><block type="quest_Note_1_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="MMsp!SS)~?)L=cxJAYN["><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="yTv,Brz.KDOk}5+?sy7j"><field name="TEXT">Reliable/Faster Response If Screen_Led_Graphics After Important Action Blocks Above</field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="}+IKagixl1:?V`F5=,b}"><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="W!._|$8d.`m72?EiQ1-B"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></shadow></value><statement name="DO0"><block type="quest_Note_3_quest_Show_String_For_Note_Small_Func" id="4Pqi~7/N@C.9Bk=D3L|q"><value name="textStrIn"><shadow type="text" id="fyt,CH;b?)SAe9GUNR:`"><field name="TEXT">Main upgrade from Lv1 to Lv2 is replacing cpu_laggy 'show leds' block with cpu_fast 'plox x _ y _' block, such as below: </field></shadow></value><next><block type="controls_if" id="v:b_TfE:bX|gv)l1m_*2"><mutation elseif="4" else="1"></mutation><value name="IF0"><shadow type="logic_boolean" id="xV@4n6U^*CKS`JTaa_?s"><field name="BOOL">FALSE</field></sh